con:testCase.name: Activation_TollContract
con:testCase.con:description:
USE CASE 2.2.1.1 Activate toll contract [UC-BAG-01-01]
DESCRIPTION The purpose of this use case is to process a request for activation of the BAG toll contract. A request is created by CRM and passed to TP via ESB. It is possible to receive more requests in one message. TP does not trigger any action towards OBP or TC based on those requests.
ACTORS CRM, NAV4/ODS, ESB, TP
PRE-CONDITIONS Masterdata Customer, Address, Contact, TollContract (not active) lists are processed in TPL The test may be executed in various environments due to proprietary addresses.
POST-CONDITIONS The TollContract is Processed in TPL, all mandatory data are in mandatory tables, TollContractStatus is sent to ESB
NORMAL COURSE N1 TP receives TollContractOperation request [ActionCode = 1] from CRM via TollContractOperation service. TP creates new TollContractOperation record. N2 TP validates TollContractOperation request [ActionCode = 1]. Validation is OK. N3 TP prepares TollContractStatus response [ActionCode = 1]. TP creates new TollContractStatus record. N4 TP sends TollContractStatus response to CRM via TollContractStatus service [ActionCode = 1]. UC ends.
ALTERNATIVE COURSE [N2] Validation of TollContractOperation request [ActionCode = 1] is not OK. UC continues with N3.
EXCEPTION COURSE *********** NOT INCLUDED IN THIS TEST CASE DUE TO a LONG TIME TO PROCESSING /* [N1] TP is not able to process the TollContractOperation request. E1 TP creates a new Alert record. UC ends. */
TEST CASE in SOAPUI DESCRIPTION Simply info. We use pre-generated data in Test Cases: Masterdata MasterData_Customer_Address_Contact_list MasterData_TollContract_list where are inclueded groovy steps "values generators". First sent and Processing TollContract list is with inactive TollContract. Cause of it we need to send Masterdata 2 times, once before the Test Case, and after processing TollContract flow. Prerequisities for these test is run of these Test Cases without error: MasterData_Customer_Address_Contact_list MasterData_TollContract_list PREREQUISITES FOR ALL MASTERDATA: All Masterdata have the same Body. All non-constant data are randomized. These first 2 steps prepare data for Customer, Address, Contact... in both TPCore and Telematic Database. TollContract Operation SOAP message sent from NAV4 to ESB where ESB converts the SOAP message into the REST message and sends this message into TPCore. TPCore process all incoming data (REST messages) TPCore validates all data TPCore creates and process TollContractStatus TPCore try to send TollContractStatus to NAV4 throw the WSO2, ESB TPCore receive the MasterData TollContract list (TollContract Active) and process him TPCore update mtd.TollContract table
PREREQUISITES for all SoapUI Test Cases All Masterdata have the same Body. All non-constant data are randomized. The test may be executed in various environments due to proprietary addresses. If something fails, start a Negative Test Case. Test Case must be run in TestRunner with the parameter "Do not stop if error occurs, ignore them " (IF Jenkins Available use Chrono to run this Test Case after each release), or by play from SoapUI Test Case In Test, Runner must be sett-up the Report way and report folder. If all is OK, step TollContractStatus_sent_NOK won't be executed
NORMAL COURSES N1 If all is OK, step TollContractStatus_sent_NOK won't be executed 1. MasterData load - ODS-ESB - "run TestCase MasterData_Customer_Address_Contact_list" and "run TestCase MasterData_TollContract_list" steps 2. action - prepares UUID for navigating throw all the flow - is mandatory for all SOAP/REST calls 3. TollcontractOperation1_SOAP-NAV4-ESB_Activation - message to ESB which start sending REST message to the TPCore throw the WSO2, to start the TollContract Activation process 4. Action is DONE: TPCore Process the data from TollcontractOperation message, validates them, and end with ProcessStatus 100 5. TollContractStatus_sent_OK - TPCore prepares TollContractStatus and process him into sending table OutgoingMessage 6. OutgoingMessage_OK - TPCore process TollContractStatus and on the end sends TollContractStatus to the ESB throw the WSO2 7. run TestCase MasterData_TollContract_list_tollContractStatus_0 - This Test Steps RUN MasterData TollContract list (Active) flow with all of the processing assertions 8. mtd.TollContract - this step check the MasterData TollContract list is processed 9. After it the flows continue on the end of Test Case "clean all"
NEG: PREREQUISITES validation of TollcontractOperation is not OK or missing some data Main Causes: The MasterData were not correctly processed The data from MasterData call is not in mtd table The TPCore received duplicate ActionId The TPCore received not valid TollcontractOperation The TPCore received TollcontractOperation with leading to the same data in processing state The TPCore received TollcontractOperation with leading to data, not in active state (not Active TollContract) 1. MasterData load - ODS-ESB - "run TestCase MasterData_Customer_Address_Contact_list" and "run TestCase MasterData_TollContract_list" steps 2. ActionId - prepares UUID for navigating throw the all the flow - is mandatory for all SOAP/REST calls 3. TollcontractOperation1_SOAP-NAV4-ESB_Activation - message to ESB which start sending REST message to the TPCore throw the WSO2, to start the TollContract Activation process 4. Action is DONE: TPCore Process the data from TollcontractOperation message, validates them, and end with ProcessStatus -1, -2, -3 or -4 5. IF mtd.TollContract step doesn't have a response, or in Test Step "Action is DONE" is another ProcessStatus, The Test Case Continues with TollContractStatus_sent_NOK and after it OutgoingMessage_OK_2 6. TollContractStatus_sent_NOK - this Test Step validate the NEGative TollContractStatus is processed and prepared to send 7. OutgoingMessage_OK_2 - this Test Step validate the NEGative TollContractStatus is sent to ESB throw the WSO2
POSSIBLE EXCEPTION COURSES by MANIPULATING WITH TEST CASE !!!!!!PRE-PREREQUISITES!!!!!! save these project: "EETS_DE" and lead him to not make an error in the main branch PREREQUISITES We do not test mainly MasterData send, in this Test Case, but if it fails, it's not a succeeded prerequisite. con:testCase.con:description:
USE CASE 2.3.2.1 Activate toll contract [UC-VPS-01-01] DESCRIPTION The purpose of this use case is to process a request for activation of Viapass toll contract. A request is created by CRM and passed to TP via ESB. It is possible to receive more requests in one message. TP does not trigger any action towards OBP or TC based on those requests. ACTORS CRM, NAV4/ODS, ESB, TP NORMAL COURSE N1 TP receives TollContractOperation request [ActionCode = 1] from CRM via TollContractOperation service. TP creates new TollContractOperation record. N2 TP validates TollContractOperation request [ActionCode = 1]. Validation is OK.
TEST CASE in SOAPUI version 4.0 DESCRIPTION Simply info. We use pregenerated data in first 31 groovy steps. Cause of it we need sent Masterdata 2 times. Because of this test, we use firstly step ODS-ESB which convert message to two and send 2 same MasterData messages at same time with another Header. TollContract Operation sent from NAV4 to ESB where ESB converts SOAP message into REST message and send this message into TPCore. This first step prepare data for Customer, Address, Contact... in both TPCore and Telematic Database.
PREREQUISITIES for all SOAPUI Test Cases All Masterdata have same Body. All non-constant data are randomized. Test may be executed in various environments due to proprietary addresses. If something fail, start Negative Test Case. Test Case must be run in TestRunner with parameter "Do not stop if error occures, ignore them ". In Test Runner must be setuped the Report way and report folder. If all is OK, step TollContractStatus_sent_NOK wont be executed
NORMAL COURSES N1 If all is OK, step TollContractStatus_sent_NOK wont be executed 1. MasterData load - ODS-ESB 2. save to json - saves previous step into 2. TollContractOperation - NAV4-ESB 3. MasterData load - ESB-TLM 4. MasterData load - ESB-TPL 5. MasterData TPCore checks 6. IF error GO TO TollContractStatus_sent_NOK and checks sending of TollContractStatus_sent_NOK 7. clean all - clean all creating
N2 PREREQUISITIES Disable "TollcontractOperation1_SOAP-NAV4-ESB_Activation" step. Enable "TollcontractOperation2_REST-ESB-TPL_Activation" Enable "Groovy Conditional GOTO2" If all is OK, step TollContractStatus_sent_NOK wont be executed
1. MasterData load - ODS-ESB 2. save to json - saves previous step into 2. TollContractOperation - ESB-TPL 3. MasterData load - ESB-TLM 4. MasterData load - ESB-TPL 5. MasterData TPCore checks 6. IF error some of the TPCore checks GO TO TollContractStatus_sent_NOK and checks sending of TollContractStatus_sent_NOK 7. clean all - clean all creating
EXCEPTION COURSES PREREQUISITIES We do not testing mainly MasterData send, in this Test Case, but if it fail, its not succeeded prerequisition. We simulate bad request by deleting one row of json in step 1 E1 1. MasterData load - ODS-ESB - fail
E2 We do not testing mainly MasterData send, in this Test Case, but if it fail, its not succeeded prerequisition. ESB NOT convert MasterData message to two and send 2 same MasterData messages at same time with another Header. We simulate bad request by deleting one row of json in step 3
1. MasterData load - SOAP - ODS-ESB - OK 2. TollContractOperation - ESB-TPL - OK 3. MasterData load - REST - ESB-TPL - fail
E3 PREREQUISITIES We do not testing mainly MasterData send, in this Test Case, but if it fail, its not succeeded prerequisition. ESB NOT convert MasterData message to two and send 2 same MasterData messages at same time with another Header. OK means Test Step passed. fail means Test Step ends with error. We simulate bad request by deleting one row of json in step 4
1. MasterData load - SOAP - ODS-ESB - OK 2. TollContractOperation - ESB-TPL -OK 3. MasterData load - REST - ESB-TPL - OK 4. MasterData load - REST - ESB-TLM - fail
